SUMMARY:Five Day Cake Baking & Decorating Masterclass
DESCRIPTION:If you’ve always dreamed of being a cake decorator\, this 5-day masterclass is the perfect introduction to Cakes! \nThis class is perfect for absolute beginners! This is a 5 day course running for 5 hours each day. \nOUTLINE \n\nDAY 1: FOUNDATIONS OF CAKE BAKING AND BUTTERCREAM MAKING\nDAY 2: MAKING A RAINBOW STRIPED CAKE\nDAY 3: FLORAL BUTTERCREAM PIPING TECHNIQUES\nDay 4: INTRODUCTION TO GUMPASTE AND FONDANT\nDay 5: STACKING & DECORATING A TWO TIERED CAKE\n\nDAY 1: FOUNDATIONS OF CAKE BAKING AND BUTTERCREAM MAKING \n\nMix\, colour and bake a vanilla cake\nMake swiss meringue buttercream in groups\nLearn how to colour buttercream\nLearn how to use a piping bag and practicing piping design techniques\n\nDAY 2: MAKING A RAINBOW STRIPED CAKE \n\nLearn how to cut and layer your colourful cake\nLearn how to use essential cake tools to achieve smooth straight sides on your cake\nLearn how create rainbow coloured stripes on the sides of your cake\n\nDAY 3: FLORAL BUTTERCREAM PIPING TECHNIQUES \n\nHow to use piping bags and tips to decorate cupcakes with buttercream\nHow to pipe a rose\, 5 petal flower and mum\nHow to pipe leaves and foliage to complete your cupcakes\n\nDay 4: INTRODUCTION TO GUMPASTE AND FONDANT \n\nWhere to buy and how to store fondant and gumpaste\nHow to colour and mix fondant and gumpaste\nHow to use essential cake tools to achieve smooth straight sides on your cake\nHow to cover your cake in fondant and which tools to use\nHow to use fondant cutouts to decorate and finish your cake\nHow to add proper supports to your gumpaste teddy bear before placing on your finished cake\n\nDay 5: STACKING & DECORATING A TWO TIERED CAKE \n\nHow to use piping bags and colours to decorate your cake\nHow to use essential cake tools to achieve smooth straight sides on you cake\nHow to properly add supports and stack a two tiered cake\n\nYou will go home with: \n\nA one tier 6’’ round tall rainbow cake that you will have decorated yourself on Day 2\nbuttercream flower cupcakes from Day 3\nA  fondant cake with gumpaste topper that you will have created on Day 4\nA two tiered buttercream cake flower cake on Day 5\nChocolate cake recipe\, vanilla cake recipe\, Swiss meringue and American buttercream recipe\, emailed to you at the time of your booking\n‘How to use piping tips’ recipe emailed to you at the time of your booking\n\nPictures are for display purposes only. Your teacher will talk you through design elements in any picture shown\, but for efficient running of this class\, you will be guided by her in terms of design. \nAll ingredients and equipment\, including transport boxes\, for your cake course are provided\, you do not need to bring anything with you. The teacher will ensure that you work at a pace suitable for you. \nIf you would like\, you can bring a large bag to carry your cake(s) home. We provide sturdy cardboard boxes\, but you may find it easier to carry your cake(s) in a reusable tote bag especially if taking public transit to class.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/five-day-cake-baking-decorating-masterclass/
LOCATION:12 Sousa Mendes Street\, 12 Sousa Mendes St\, Toronto\, ON M6P 0A8\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M6P 0A8
CATEGORIES:Classes & Workshops,Food & Drink
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/five-day-cake-baking-decorating-masterclass.png
END:VEVENT
