SUMMARY:HOMAGE TO THE KOBZAR -  Bandura Recital
DESCRIPTION:Bandurist Victor Mishalow has made a significant contribution to  Ukrainian music in Canada\, both through his performances and writings.  He formed the original Canadian Bandurist Capella in 1991\, and  introduced many young people to this ancient Ukrainian instrument. Born  in Sydney\, Australia\, Victor was the first person in that country to do  his high school practical music performance exam on the bandura. Since  then\, Victor has made it his life’s passion and work. He graduated from  Sydney University with a double major in Musicology and  Ethno-Musicology\, and did his postgraduate studies at the Kyiv  Conservatory for master’s in music. Victor has performed in North  America\, Europe and Australia\, and has played solo performances in  Carnegie Hall\, Massey Hall\, and the Sydney Opera House. He completed  several concert tours in Ukraine\, with over 70 solo concert recitals. \nTickets: $35Children under 12 – free Date: Monday\, March 9\, 2026 Time: 6-8 PM Address: 1604 Bloor Street West\, Toronto \nTickets: https://www.shevchenko.ca/events/details.cfm?eventid=2187 \nIf you wish to purchase tickets by phone\, please call the museum at 416-534-8662
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/homage-to-the-kobzar-bandura-recital/
LOCATION:SHEVCHENKO MUSEUM • LIBRARY • GALLERIES\, 1604 Bloor St W\, Toronto\, ON M6P 1A7\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M6P 1A7
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Cultural Celebrations,Live Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/homage-to-the-kobzar-bandura-recital.png
END:VEVENT
